Legs (
Figs. 112, 114 – 116
) long and slender; procoxae subglobose, mesocoxae oval, metacoxae strongly transverse; all trochanters short; all femora moderately strongly clavate; tibiae and tarsi long and slender. Males of all species have variously shaped projections on ventral margin of metafemora (
Figs. 117–120
).

Aedeagus (
Figs. 121–128
) elongate and moderately darkly sclerotized, relatively thin-walled, with symmetrical median lobe and symmetrical, complicated assemblage of internal sclerites; parameres free and slender, with apical setae.
